<plot>A filmed account of how deaf photographer Emma Amsden has overcome her disability to comunicate through her still images. Filmmaker Jim Moran, himself an award-winning photographer, is dyslexic. The Exchange considers their varying approaches to their work in pictures.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?555979</url></doc>
